question: Angela Dorothea Kasner
answer: Angela Dorothea Kasner (born 17 July 1954) is a German politician who served as Chancellor of Germany from 2005 to 2017. She is a member of the Christian Democratic Union (CDU).  Kasner was born in Hamburg, West Germany, the daughter of Horst Kasner, a Lutheran pastor, and his wife Herlind, a teacher. Kasner grew up in Templin in Brandenburg. She studied physics at the University of Leipzig from 1973 to 1978.  Kasner is married to Joachim Sauer, a quantum chemist who has taught at the Humboldt University of Berlin since 1992. The couple has two sons, born in 1986 and 1991.  Kasner started her career as a research scientist at the Central Institute for Physical Chemistry of the Academy of Sciences in East Berlin. She later became a scientific assistant at the Institute for Energy and Environmental Research in Heidelberg.  Kasner has been a member of the CDU since 1981. She was a member of the Bundestag, the German parliament, from 1990 to 2005, and served as Minister for Women and Youth from 1998 to 2005.  Kasner was elected Chancellor of Germany in 2005, succeeding Gerhard Schröder of the Social Democratic Party (SPD). She was reelected in 2009 and 2013. In November 2016, she announced that she would not seek a fourth term as Chancellor, and would retire from politics at the end of her term in 2017.

question: Mostrami i percorsi nel Grand Canyon in cui non ci sono pericoli di inondazioni istantanee.
answer: Il Grand Canyon è una grande gola scavata nella roccia, lunga oltre 400 km, situata nel nord-ovest degli Stati Uniti. La parte più alta del canyon raggiunge i 2.500 metri di altitudine, mentre il fondo si trova a circa 1.000 metri di profondità. Il Grand Canyon è stato scavato dal fiume Colorado, che scorre lungo il suo letto. Il pericolo di inondazioni istantanee è minimo, poiché il fiume Colorado è un corso d'acqua molto lento.

question: War die Kubakrise vor der Schweinebuchtinvasion?
answer: Die Kubakrise begann 1962, als die Sowjetunion auf die Insel Kuba Militärbasen errichtete. Die USA sahen dies als Bedrohung an und verhängten ein Embargo gegen Kuba. Im April 1961 hatte die CIA einen Militärputsch in Kuba gegen Fidel Castro geführt, der gescheitert war. Die USA befürchteten, dass die Sowjetunion nun eine Basis in Kuba haben würde, von der aus sie die USA angreifen könnte. Die Kubakrise eskalierte, als die Sowjetunion auch Atomwaffen auf Kuba stationierte. Die USA schickten Flugzeuge in die Schweinebucht, um die Atomwaffen zu vernichten. Die Kubakrise wurde durch die Schweinebuchtinvasion beendet, als die USA die Insel besetzten.

question: Di quali ingredienti ho bisogno per la torta di carote?
answer: Ingredienti:  2 uova  100 gr di farina  100 gr di zucchero  100 gr di carote  1 bustina di lievito  1 cucchiaino di cannella  50 ml di olio di semi  Come si prepara?  1. Preriscaldate il forno a 180°C.  2. Sbattete le uova con lo zucchero fino a renderle chiare e spumose.  3. Grattugiate le carote e uniteli all’uovo, quindi aggiungete la farina, il lievito e la cannella.  4. Versate l’olio di semi e mescolate bene il tutto.  5. Imburrate e infarinate una tortiera da 22 cm di diametro e versate il composto.  6. Cuocete la torta di carote in forno per circa 35-40 minuti, o fino a quando sarà dorata in superficie.  7. Sfornatela e lasciatela raffreddare prima di servirla.

question: Dar mim a tempo de execução do Brinquedo História.
answer: A história do Brinquedo é uma história de amor. Um amor que nasceu do nada e que cresceu a cada dia, conquistando corações e espalhando alegria. Esse amor é o amor pelo brinquedo.  Um dia, um menino encontrou um brinquedo na rua. Era uma boneca de pano, bem simples, mas ele a adorou. Ele a levou para casa e a cuidou como se fosse a coisa mais importante do mundo.  A boneca se tornou o seu melhor amigo. Ele a levava para todos os lugares e contava para ela todas as suas histórias. Ele a amava muito.  Um dia, o menino foi para a escola e deixou a boneca em casa. Quando voltou, a boneca tinha desaparecido. Ele ficou muito triste e procurou por ela por toda a cidade, mas não a encontrou.  Finalmente, ele desistiu e foi para a escola. No meio da aula, ele olhou para o lado e viu a boneca, sentada ao seu lado. Ele ficou muito feliz e abraçou-a forte.  O amor pelo brinquedo é um amor que nunca acaba.

question: Arată-mi autobiografia lui Hemingway
answer: Born in Oak Park, Illinois, on July 21, 1899, Hemingway was the son of a doctor and the grandson of a prominent judge. He grew up in a comfortable middle-class home and was educated in the public schools of Chicago.  In 1917 Hemingway joined the Kansas City Star as a cub reporter. The following year he volunteered as an ambulance driver in Italy with the American Field Service. He was severely wounded in 1918 while serving with the Italian infantry and was decorated with the Silver Medal of Military Valor.  After the war Hemingway returned to the United States and married Hadley Richardson. The couple moved to Paris, where Hemingway worked as a foreign correspondent for the Toronto Star. He began to write fiction in the 1920s and achieved critical and popular success with his novels The Sun Also Rises (1926), A Farewell to Arms (1929), and For Whom the Bell Tolls (1940).  During World War II Hemingway served as a correspondent in London and Paris and was decorated with the Legion of Honor and the Croix de Guerre. In 1954 he was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature. Hemingway spent the last years of his life in Idaho, where he committed suicide on July 2, 1961.
